        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ جُعْلِ اَلْآبِقِ وَ اَلضَّالَّةِ قَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4060 - It is narrated from Wahb ibn Wahb, from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) from his father, Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), who said:\nI asked Imam (as) about the reward for returning a runaway slave or lost property.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it.\""
        ]
      }
